post_text:
School pictures at South Jefferson High School and Middle School will take place on Tuesday 9/15 for students with the last names A - L. Students with last names M - Z will have school pictures on Thursday 9/17.

You child was given a picture packet in their homeroom either on Wednesday or Thursday of this week. However, in order to encourage a contactless experience, and minimize contact as much as possible, BJK Photography and SJ are encouraging parents to order their student's photos online at www.bjkphotos.com. There is a blue ORDER HERE link in the upper right hand corner of the page.

ALL REMOTE students will be welcomed into the school from 2:00pm - 3:00pm on the day corresponding with their last name for photos. Parents needing a different time earlier in the photo session can call Mr. Ginger's office at 315.232.4531 ext. 2910, to arrange to visit the building earlier in the day. BJK is not available for photographs after 3:00pm.

Thank you, and don't forget to smile!

Mr. Ginger

post_text: Happy Friday Spartans. Our wonderful Food Service team has been hard at work this summer processing local produce for the upcoming school year. Lots of tomatoes, beans, squash, swiss chard, fresh herbs and zucchini have been chopped, shredded, blanch and put away for our students to enjoy in the fall. Over 200 pounds of zucchini and squash from Adams was shredded for our homemade breads, muffins and soups. We are so excited to see our students back in our buildings, and to have the opportunity to continue feeding them wholesome, homemade meals! #greenisgood #buylocal #growingminds #zucchinifordays

post_text:
South Jefferson Parents,
There is a very important survey that needs to be submitted to the district on behalf of each student who attends South Jefferson. Its purpose is gathering student-specific information the district needs to plan for transportation, technology, and our hybrid model for school in the fall. We are still waiting for responses from the parents of 478 students.

In order to submit the survey, parents MUST log into their ParentSquare account. The data is specific to your child and as such REQUIRES a login. This morning I sent an account invitation (via email or text) to all the SJ parents who have not yet activated their account. Please use the activation code/link in the invite to log into your parentsquare account and fill out the survey titled "Reopening Survey #2".

If you have not submitted the survey because you are in need of technical assistance, please send an email to helpforparents@spartanpride.org. Provide your phone number and a good time to call and someone from the school will give you a call to walk you through the process.

Northern New York Community Foundation
July 22 at 10:15 AM ·

Congratulations to Caden Lucas!

Caden is this recipient of the Northern New York Community Foundation Robert E. & Dora M. Belcher Memorial Scholarship. A 2020 graduate of South Jefferson CSD, Caden will attend Paul Smith's College this fall to study fisheries and wildlife science. Caden is the son of Brandy and Jeff Lucas, Adams Center.

The Robert E. & Dora M. Belcher Memorial Scholarship is awarded annually to students pursuing careers in environmental or ecological studies or a related field.

Pictured, from left: Joseph Malatino, wife, Marianne, daughter of Robert E. and Dora Belcher, and scholarship recipient Caden Lucas.

#NNYCF #ClassOf2020 #Scholars

*please share...

Good Morning,

To alleviate some possible confusion, I want to clarify pick up expectations for educational materials. This message only refers to HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT MATERIALS.

The vast majority of high school students WILL NOT have items to pick up at the high school during the hours communicated by Mr. Slater.

ONLY families who indicated on the Family Resource Survey that they have LIMITED INTERNET CONNECTIVITY or NO INTERNET will have hard copies of materials packaged for pick up from the high school.

We will communicate directly with families that have materials here to pick up, after pick up hours are over. If you feel that you can manage without picking up materials for your high school student, please do not come to school during pick up this week.

We will be handing out materials to ALL STUDENTS in grades K-8 during pick up hours this week.

Thank you,
Jeff Ginger

Today, each child will bring home the attached letter related to the COVID-19 virus (coronavirus). Please take a moment to read this important parent notification.

I will also be meeting with school officials from other districts and officials from Public Health this week to continue talking about prevention and precautions. At this point, the flu is more of a concern for us. Protocols to help mitigate the spread of COVID-19 are the exact protocols we use to reduce the spread of the flu or cold viruses. They include:
Thorough hand washing
Covering coughs and sneezes
Staying home when a fever is present (and for 24 hours after not having signs of a fever)
I will continue to share updates as more information becomes available from the CDC, the NYS Department of Health, and the NYS Education Department.

Scott Brayley SlaterSuperintendent

Wilson Friends please join us!

Our PTO is once again sponsoring a Wacky Science Night! The science night will be held on Friday, February 28th from 6:00-8:00 p.m. This year we are inviting students to join the wacky world of science by completing their OWN science projects. (prior approval from submitting the project application Form)

Student science projects and display boards will be set-up in the gyms, hallway and cafeteria. Students will share their projects throughout the evening. There will be hands-on science experiments and exhibits set-up in both gymnasiums and the cafeteria for students and families to visit. Be sure to stop by the Scholastic Book Fair and pick out some great books too!

We are looking forward to this FUN, WACKY event!!!

Career Chats for HS Students:
Guidance would like to announce some upcoming Career Chats!
*On Thursday, December 19th, Mrs. Kristin LaClair will be here to talk with students during Mrs. Garza's 3rd period class. Mrs. LaClair is the Director for the Children's Miracle Network Hospitals of NNY. She works out of Samaritan Medical Center. She obtained a Bachelor's Degree in Childhood Education from SUNY Oswego followed by a Masters Degree in Curriculum and Instruction. Any student interested in attending should speak to their School Counselor for a permission slip.
*On Tuesday, Dec. 10th Ms. Kayla Perry will be here to talk in Mrs. Garza's 3rd period class. Ms. Perry is currently the Director of Events for the Greater Watertown North Country Chamber of Commerce. Ms. Perry graduated from Oswego State with a Bachelors Degree in Marketing. Any student interested in Marketing, Communications, Human Resource Management , etc. or in Oswego's program is encouraged to attend. Please see your School Counselor for a permission slip.

post_text:
Adopt-A-Platoon

Wilson Elementary has adopted a Black Hawk helicopter company the “Warlords” they are a part of Task Force Phoenix Platoon. They are currently deployed to Afghanistan. On Veterans Day they flew a flag that they will be sending to our school soon. This is a wonderful opportunity to support our local military during their deployment and remind them that their services are valued and appreciated.

Each month the Wilson building will be sending out cards/letters and items that will hopefully make our soldiers smile. If you have any ideas or suggestions that could help us with this project, please feel free to email Michelle Kramer -mkramer@spartanpride.org. We will be collecting items from now until June and then dispersing them each month with our cards/letters and other projects.

We truly appreciate your support with this opportunity to support our local service members and their families.

A list of items the soldiers may need will be included in the monthly newsletter.

post_text: After an amazing week of preparation, our Food Service Staff is excited to serve the district our annual “Thanksgiving Dinner”! We would like to share some numbers with you all: 320 pounds of turkey, 150 pounds of diced bread (for some from-scratch stuffing), 44 gallons of Turkey gravy, and 1487 dinner rolls (fresh, hand rolled Thursday morning) and more!!! We are grateful for the beautiful local veggies and herbs to help amp up this awesome day! #andapartridgeinapeartree #scratchcooking #servedwithlove #growingminds

post_text: Thank you to the Annie Porter Ainsworth Memorial Library in Sandy Creek for returning some long lost books to the Clarke Library! The 5 Volume Complete Works of Edgar Allen Poe were last checked out in 1974 and were recently re-discovered by a patron when cleaning out a camp. The books are copyright 1903 and will be added to our library's archive collection.

post_text:
Wilson elementary celebrating Veterans Day

In observation of Veterans Day our third grade had a presentation from our very own Mr. and Mrs. Dalrymple! Both are Army veterans. Third grade students gathered in the gym to hear about expectations of life as a military soldier. Students and staff played games and even had the opportunity to put on a military uniform! Students also learned how to do a proper military salute from Mr. and Mrs. Dalrymple.

post_text:
The SJ Girls Swim Team set 5 school records and placed 6th at he Section 3 Championships Friday.
The 200 Medley Relay of Julia Garvin, Ava Burns, Carley Hughes, and Emma Purvis broke the school record with a time of 2:04.39 and placed 5th.
Ava Burns then set the school record in the 200 I.M. with a time of 2:29.05 and placed 11th.
Emma Purvis then set the school record in the 100 freestyle with a time of 56.99 and placed 5th. Emma also placed 7th in the 50 freestyle.
Julia Garvin broke the school record in the 100 Backstroke with a time of 1:08.65 and placed 9th
The 200 yard freestyle relay of Morgan Burt, Julia Garvin, and Lauren Covey placed 6th
The girls then finished the day setting the school record in the 400 freestyle relay. The team of Ava Burns, Laura Zehr, Carley Hughes, and Emma Purvis placed 6th.
